        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 3:18PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lynn, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lynn, Double Springs, Poplar Springs, Houston Recreational Area, Camp
McDowell, Ashbank, Smith Lake, Natural Bridge, Clear Creek, Curtis
Crossroads, and Black Pond.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
